data.title: Zico To Open For Wiz Khalifa’s Solo Concert In Seoul

data.text:
Wiz Khalifa‘s Seoul concert is set to be one straight out of a hip-hop fan’s dreams as Zico and BewhY have been confirmed to join as opening acts.

Wiz Khalifa will be holding a concert at Jamsil Sports Complex in Seoul on May 3. Opening for Khalifa will be Show Me the Money Season 5 winner, BewhY as well as Block B‘s Zico.

Zico’s presence in the Korean rap scene has been constantly growing over the past few years. With his appearances on many rap shows as a mentor such as Show Me the Money, he has become one of the industries most respected names.

The concert will mark Wiz Khalifa’s first time performing in Korea since his misunderstanding with Girl’s Generation‘s Taeyeon at the 2016 MAMA. It is expected that Bill Tex and DPR LIVE will also perform at the concert completing the lineup for the night. It is sure to be an exciting event, showcasing an excellent mix of Korean and Western hip-hop.

Check out Wiz Khalifa’s last performance at the 2016 MAMA awards below.

Source: Dispatch
